CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 24, 1945, pg. 9, reads: "Plan Health Week Program - The Health Education Committee of Centre Avenue Branch YWCA is planning a constructive program for the celebration of National Negro Health Week, April 1 to 8. A mass meeting will be held Sunday, April 8, and Dr. Horace C. Scott, State deputy secretary of health, will be the principal speaker.  in photo, left to right, are Mrs. M. E.. Edmunds, Miss Lettie Ayers, Miss Helen Clark, Mrs. Wilhelmina R. Owens, health education secretary; Mrs. Aline Hurd, chairman of the committee; Mrs. Corrine Armstrong, Mrs. Edna Morris and Mrs. Phillis Harris. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mrs. M. E. Edmunds, Lettie Ayers, Helen Clark, Wilhelmina R. Owens, Aline Hurd, Corrine Armstrong, Edna Morris, and Phillis Harris, gathered around table in Centre Avenue YWCA
